## §3. QIINT2-VALIDATOR API REUSE

### §3.1 Functions da exist (session-20260420-final/qiint2/qiint2-validator.ts)

| Function | Input | Output | K1 use |
|---|---|---|---|
| `computePiBody()` | BodyMetrics | number | cell body health check |
| `computePiMedium()` | MediumMetrics | number | cell medium health check |
| `computePiSubstrate()` | SubstrateMetrics | number | cell substrate health check |
| `computeRecoveryPotential()` | RecoveryCapabilities | number | thoai-sinh capability score |
| `classifyVerdict()` | (piBody, piMedium, piSubstrate, recovery) | Verdict | 6-class verdict |
| `tempToNauionState()` | temp | 7-state | chromatic state output |
| `validateCell()` | input | CellReport | full cycle |
| `batchReport()` | reports[] | BatchReport | system-wide state |

### §3.2 Verdict → K1 Output Contract Mapping

SPEC_QIINT_PHYSICS_FOUNDATION §2.1 quy dinh K1 output:
```
ACCEPT | BACKPRESSURE | LOAD_SHED | CIRCUIT_BREAK
```

qiint2-validator classifyVerdict() cho 6 verdict. Map:

| qiint2 verdict | K1 output | Action |
|---|---|---|
| `healthy` | ACCEPT | signal pass through |
| `substrate_fail` | BACKPRESSURE | degrade substrate load |
| `medium_fail` | BACKPRESSURE | restore snapshot + degrade |
| `body_drift` | BACKPRESSURE | re-anchor orbital + degrade |
| `revivable_death` | LOAD_SHED | priority-based shed + thoai-sinh trigger |
| `permanent_death` | CIRCUIT_BREAK | auto-trip + half-open recovery |

